Introduction
************

This is the README for `continual-sync', a tool to keep a directory
synchronised with its mirror as efficiently and quickly as possible.  It
uses rsync and the inotify change notification mechanism to ensure that
rsync does as little work as possible.


Documentation
*************

Manual pages are included in this distribution.  See `man continual-sync',
`man watchdir', and `man continual-sync.conf'.


Compilation
***********

To compile the package, type `make'.  Use `make install' to install it.


